The paper proposes a method for multi-task learning (MTL) that focuses on interpretability and deals with data from heterogeneous domains. The method is based on boosted trees, which are commonly used in machine learning for classification and regression tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these sub-categories are closely related to the topic of MTL and boosted trees. Additionally, the paper mentions regularization and early-stopping mechanisms, which are techniques commonly used in optimization and could place the paper in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper also mentions interpretability, which is a topic of interest in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
